00:39:17.280 --> 00:39:19.320
And the main sticking
point-- and we

00:39:19.320 --> 00:39:21.445
were speaking about this,
in the green room, again.

00:39:21.445 --> 00:39:24.190
If only you'd been in the green
room, everything happened.

00:39:24.190 --> 00:39:26.940
The main thing that everybody
was rallying against,

00:39:26.940 --> 00:39:28.950
as you were saying,
that trans rights

00:39:28.950 --> 00:39:31.920
are 20 years behind gay
rights, is everybody's beef

00:39:31.920 --> 00:39:32.850
was with trans.

00:39:32.850 --> 00:39:35.010
And they were using
the same rhetoric

00:39:35.010 --> 00:39:39.277
that was used about gay
people 20 years ago.

00:39:39.277 --> 00:39:40.860
20 years ago, it
would've been, you're

00:39:40.860 --> 00:39:41.970
trying to turn my kid gay.

00:39:41.970 --> 00:39:45.360
It's like, no-- born that way.

00:39:45.360 --> 00:39:46.950
Now you're starting to get it.

00:39:46.950 --> 00:39:49.530
But they're not
there yet with trans.

00:39:49.530 --> 00:39:53.295
But education has gotten
people to a certain point.

00:39:53.295 --> 00:39:54.920
But there's a lot
more education to do.

00:39:54.920 --> 00:39:57.050
So I don't know if
policing is going to do it.

00:39:57.050 --> 00:39:58.950
But getting people
who are more educated,

00:39:58.950 --> 00:40:01.590
people who are actually
questioning, and as you said,

00:40:01.590 --> 00:40:06.270
sort of normalizing the
situation, usualizing it.

00:40:06.270 --> 00:40:09.120
As that happens,
we can only hope

00:40:09.120 --> 00:40:10.840
that that will not be there.

00:40:10.840 --> 00:40:13.200
Because we also rely on
our freedom of speech

00:40:13.200 --> 00:40:14.550
to be able to fight back.

00:40:14.550 --> 00:40:17.519
We can't fight back against
it if we're being silenced

00:40:17.519 --> 00:40:18.810
and if we're all being policed.

00:40:18.810 --> 00:40:22.030
JULIEN FINLAY: Yeah, and
