00:40:41.680 --> 00:40:45.160
And if we could go to--

00:40:45.160 --> 00:40:46.270
well, yeah.

00:40:46.270 --> 00:40:52.940
So that's a quote from a Jewish
sociologist, who does say

00:40:52.940 --> 00:40:56.690
basically, tech companies
are seeing themselves

00:40:56.690 --> 00:40:57.400
as publishers.

00:40:57.400 --> 00:40:58.690
So now we are responsible.

00:40:58.690 --> 00:41:00.770
The companies will be
responsible for the content

00:41:00.770 --> 00:41:01.269
online.

00:41:05.210 --> 00:41:08.360
Who's at fault, the
messenger or the medium?

00:41:08.360 --> 00:41:09.330
Who should be policed?

00:41:09.330 --> 00:41:13.235
Who should be responsible for
the tribune that is published?

00:41:13.235 --> 00:41:14.260
Is it the journal?

00:41:14.260 --> 00:41:15.170
Is it the reader?

00:41:15.170 --> 00:41:16.610
Is it the writer?

00:41:16.610 --> 00:41:19.340
What are your thoughts?

00:41:19.340 --> 00:41:21.504
AOIFE MARTIN: I think the
medium has probably more

00:41:21.504 --> 00:41:22.670
responsibility in this area.

00:41:22.670 --> 00:41:27.350
Certainly, I know, again,
speaking about Twitter,

00:41:27.350 --> 00:41:28.730
they're quite happy to have--

00:41:28.730 --> 00:41:32.150
if somebody has a
lot of followers.

00:41:32.150 --> 00:41:34.780
Remember Milo on Twitter?

00:41:34.780 --> 00:41:37.340
