FINLAY WILSON: I think
one challenge would

00:43:22.420 --> 00:43:25.390
be perhaps for the police
and the authorities

00:43:25.390 --> 00:43:28.720
to perhaps look at
the fact that there

00:43:28.720 --> 00:43:32.950
are obvious inequalities in how
crime reporting, but also crime

00:43:32.950 --> 00:43:34.480
handling, is dealt with.

00:43:34.480 --> 00:43:38.230
So certainly when it came to
me handing over this letter,

00:43:38.230 --> 00:43:40.390
I was told, oh, we'll
take your fingerprints.

00:43:40.390 --> 00:43:41.410
We'll do it right now.

00:43:41.410 --> 00:43:42.487
They didn't.

00:43:42.487 --> 00:43:43.820
Then they said, well, come back.

00:43:43.820 --> 00:43:45.450
We'll take your fingerprints.

00:43:45.450 --> 00:43:46.469
They still didn't.

00:43:46.469 --> 00:43:48.260
They said they would
interview my neighbors

00:43:48.260 --> 00:43:49.218
to find out who it was.

00:43:49.218 --> 00:43:50.204
They didn't.

00:43:50.204 --> 00:43:51.620
Then it became a
high-profile case

00:43:51.620 --> 00:43:52.828
because I took it to the BBC.

00:43:52.828 --> 00:43:55.460
And they still didn't.

00:43:55.460 --> 00:43:57.950
So the ball was dropped
on many opportunities.

00:43:57.950 --> 00:44:01.890
So that's not uncommon
in that constituency.

00:44:01.890 --> 00:44:04.710
They say that their budget is
so stretched that they cannot

00:44:04.710 --> 00:44:05.710
investigate hate crime.

00:44:05.710 --> 00:44:08.880
So if we are encouraging people
to report more hate crime

00:44:08.880 --> 00:44:12.120
or to be more aware of it,
and for especially people who

00:44:12.120 --> 00:44:15.240
it's happening to, too feel
confident in reporting it,

00:44:15.240 --> 00:44:17.580
they need a bigger budget to
be able to investigate it.

00:44:17.580 --> 00:44:19.710
Because all the other
stuff is still happening.

00:44:19.710 --> 00:44:21.580
They're stretched thin.

00:44:21.580 --> 00:44:23.580
So I can understand
that they may not

00:44:23.580 --> 00:44:26.350
have the resources to follow
through with a lot of it.

00:44:26.350 --> 00:44:29.370
So there is that, more
resources for them to do that.

00:44:29.370 --> 00:44:32.640
But then it's like, OK,
bigger police presence.

00:44:32.640 --> 00:44:34.110
Do we want that either?

00:44:34.110 --> 00:44:35.430
Have they always been allies?

00:44:35.430 --> 00:44:37.000
Can they be allies?

00:44:37.000 --> 00:44:38.610
It's a tricky situation.

00:44:38.610 --> 00:44:42.630
But if it comes down to
education, the person who

00:44:42.630 --> 00:44:46.350
wrote the letter, everyone who
I showed the letter to, said,

00:44:46.350 --> 00:44:49.580
this is an older
person's handwriting.

00:44:49.580 --> 00:44:54.290
I was like, are these views
that are going to disappear?

00:44:54.290 --> 00:44:58.220
Or are they views that
are still current that

00:44:58.220 --> 00:45:02.150
are still being passed on
generation to generation?

00:45:02.150 --> 00:45:04.850
This is where I hope
the education part will

00:45:04.850 --> 00:45:07.880
have children identifying
with people in the playground,

00:45:07.880 --> 00:45:10.520
rather than-- it almost
seems like, certainly

00:45:10.520 --> 00:45:13.010
when I was at school, it only
after school that I was like,

00:45:13.010 --> 00:45:13.640
oh, my god.

00:45:13.640 --> 00:45:15.230
There's gay people.

00:45:15.230 --> 00:45:16.606
Oh, my god.

00:45:16.606 --> 00:45:17.480
And then I look back.

00:45:17.480 --> 00:45:19.809
And it's like, actually,
most of you were.

00:45:19.809 --> 00:45:20.600
But we didn't know.

00:45:20.600 --> 00:45:21.840
And we can identify them.

00:45:21.840 --> 00:45:22.850
So actually, to
have the education

00:45:22.850 --> 00:45:24.183
that school is really important.

00:45:24.183 --> 00:45:26.624
I had to sit through,
in my high school,

00:45:26.624 --> 00:45:29.060
an assembly with
the whole of my year

00:45:29.060 --> 00:45:32.120
gathered, where we were told
by a priest at the front

00:45:32.120 --> 00:45:34.490
that it was Adam and
Eve, not Adam and Steve.

00:45:34.490 --> 00:45:38.700
And they battered that into us.

00:45:38.700 --> 00:45:41.260
So if school is going
to move more inclusion,

00:45:41.260 --> 00:45:43.330
I look forward to seeing
how those children will

00:45:43.330 --> 00:45:44.830
go into the world.

00:45:44.830 --> 00:45:47.500
I see the young creators,
the young YouTubers,

00:45:47.500 --> 00:45:51.430
putting out a very diverse
message, a very almost

00:45:51.430 --> 00:45:53.080
sometimes gender fluid message.

00:45:53.080 --> 00:45:58.000
And see, that is so wonderful
to see, to see that.

00:45:58.000 --> 00:46:00.175
But that's a great thing.

00:46:00.175 --> 00:46:02.550
But we still need to focus on
there are people who really

00:46:02.550 --> 00:46:04.650
get left out and struggle.

00:46:04.650 --> 00:46:07.650
For example, somebody
who I teach yoga to,

00:46:07.650 --> 00:46:10.380
we picked her back up
after her parents sent her

00:46:10.380 --> 00:46:12.100
to gay conversion therapy.

00:46:12.100 --> 00:46:15.330
And so she had
needles in her fingers

00:46:15.330 --> 00:46:19.900
to try and beat the gay away.

00:46:19.900 --> 00:46:21.960
This still happens in Scotland.

00:46:21.960 --> 00:46:24.190
It can still happen in Scotland.

00:46:24.190 --> 00:46:31.160
So I would love if they
legislated that more and then

00:46:31.160 --> 00:46:33.020
included that in the education.

00:46:33.020 --> 00:46:35.540
This is how we used
to deal with this,

00:46:35.540 --> 00:46:38.217
like acknowledging some
of the painful history.

00:46:38.217 --> 00:46:40.800
I think that's been a big thing
in a lot of minority movements

00:46:40.800 --> 00:46:44.480
is you need to acknowledge some
of the wrong that's been done.

00:46:44.480 --> 00:46:47.000
Because if you don't,
how do we move forwards?

00:46:47.000 --> 00:46:49.070
This is where LGBT History
Months are actually

00:46:49.070 --> 00:46:52.010
really important
aspects as education.

00:46:52.010 --> 00:46:54.860
And I think that will be
great to see that in schools.

00:46:54.860 --> 00:46:56.693
JULIEN FINLAY: Aoife,
what are your thoughts

00:46:56.693 --> 00:46:58.820
on the next generation
of creators online?

00:46:58.820 --> 00:47:01.940
AOIFE MARTIN: I'm very,
very hopeful, actually.

00:47:01.940 --> 00:47:04.570
I grew up in the '70s and '80s,
when there was no internet

00:47:04.570 --> 00:47:06.530
and there was no [INAUDIBLE].

00:47:06.530 --> 00:47:08.330
There was none of this.

00:47:08.330 --> 00:47:10.550
And looking at
young people today,

00:47:10.550 --> 00:47:12.230
and they're much more outgoing.

00:47:12.230 --> 00:47:14.390
They're much more
accepting of who they are.

00:47:14.390 --> 00:47:15.500
They're much more
accepting of diversity.

00:47:15.500 --> 00:47:17.500
I mean, kids aren't
born bigoted, you know?

00:47:17.500 --> 00:47:19.039
They get bigotry
from other people.

00:47:19.039 --> 00:47:20.080
They get it from society.

00:47:20.080 --> 00:47:24.290
They get it from the media,
from what they see around them.

00:47:24.290 --> 00:47:26.720
And to see young kids
coming out and young kids

00:47:26.720 --> 00:47:29.040
being themselves,
it's just wonderful,

00:47:29.040 --> 00:47:32.639
and long may it last.

00:47:32.639 --> 00:47:33.680
JULIEN FINLAY: All right.

00:47:33.680 --> 00:47:35.309
I have a question.

00:47:35.309 --> 00:47:37.100
But I think I'd love
to hear your thoughts.

00:47:37.100 --> 00:47:40.910
And I'd love to hear how you
experience internet, what you

00:47:40.910 --> 00:47:43.940
think of the EU regulations.

00:47:43.940 --> 00:47:47.030
Because I have tackled
this a bit briefly.

00:47:47.030 --> 00:47:48.950
But we can go back again.

00:47:48.950 --> 00:47:53.060
So go ahead, whoever
wants to take the mic--

00:47:53.060 --> 00:47:55.049
so name and question, please.

00:47:55.049 --> 00:47:55.590
AUDIENCE: OK.

00:47:55.590 --> 00:47:56.271
Yeah.

00:47:56.271 --> 00:47:56.770
Hi.

00:47:56.770 --> 00:47:58.840
My name name's Kelsey.

00:47:58.840 --> 00:48:01.207
Before I just say my question,
Finlay, I have your book.

00:48:01.207 --> 00:48:03.040
I really appreciate the
pictures at the end.

00:48:03.040 --> 00:48:03.974
[LAUGHTER]

00:48:03.974 --> 00:48:05.724
FINLAY WILSON: Don't
give away the ending.

00:48:05.724 --> 00:48:06.897
[LAUGHTER]

00:48:07.397 --> 00:48:10.030
AUDIENCE: Really, as someone
who does create content,

00:48:10.030 --> 00:48:12.670
I wanted to ask if some of these
hateful messages that you're

00:48:12.670 --> 00:48:14.950
getting constantly
on this content

00:48:14.950 --> 00:48:17.170
is making you either
sort of second guess

00:48:17.170 --> 00:48:19.360
putting the content out
there, or even maybe

00:48:19.360 --> 00:48:22.030
revising what you're creating
because of your getting

00:48:22.030 --> 00:48:25.630
this negative images and
messaging constantly?

00:48:25.630 --> 00:48:27.922
Does that change how
you think about putting

00:48:27.922 --> 00:48:30.380
your content out there or the
things that you're producing?

00:48:30.380 --> 00:48:32.890
FINLAY WILSON: I wish
it didn't, but it does.

00:48:32.890 --> 00:48:36.780
So for example, I
was putting out--

00:48:36.780 --> 00:48:39.420
sometimes if I put up a
photo of my partner and I,

00:48:39.420 --> 00:48:42.270
sometimes I really do
question, like, OK.

00:48:42.270 --> 00:48:44.160
Why am I putting this out here?

00:48:44.160 --> 00:48:48.990
And sometimes I want it to
be just a simple sharing.

00:48:48.990 --> 00:48:51.270
But then it really easily
becomes politicized.

00:48:51.270 --> 00:48:54.660
Really easily, it becomes almost
like an aggressive sharing

00:48:54.660 --> 00:48:57.640
in retaliation to something
else that has happened.

00:48:57.640 --> 00:49:01.750
And so it does start to seep
into the posts in some way.

00:49:01.750 --> 00:49:05.910
But then sometimes, I might
then shift it and actually write

00:49:05.910 --> 00:49:06.750
that.

00:49:06.750 --> 00:49:08.160
So the image can speak.

00:49:08.160 --> 00:49:10.200
But the text can also speak.

00:49:10.200 --> 00:49:14.140
So I had a lot of
real body shaming.

00:49:14.140 --> 00:49:15.730
That was about three
or four days ago.

00:49:15.730 --> 00:49:16.710
So then I posted one.

00:49:16.710 --> 00:49:19.950
And I just wrote like
a letter to myself

00:49:19.950 --> 00:49:24.810
from me now to when I
really hated my body.

00:49:24.810 --> 00:49:26.190
And I wrote that.

00:49:26.190 --> 00:49:28.000
And a lot of people
resonated with that.

00:49:28.000 --> 00:49:30.660
But it was reactionary.

00:49:30.660 --> 00:49:33.150
But it also allowed me a
moment of self reflection.

00:49:33.150 --> 00:49:35.580
So it's frustrating in
that it does give me

00:49:35.580 --> 00:49:37.800
grounds to create material
that is reactionary.

00:49:37.800 --> 00:49:39.930
And it does put a
voice out there.

00:49:39.930 --> 00:49:42.690
But it is sometimes
tainted by the fact

00:49:42.690 --> 00:49:45.450
that it's come in from
such a negative source.

00:49:45.450 --> 00:49:48.560
So it does.

00:49:48.560 --> 00:49:50.513
And it does make
me second guess.

00:49:50.513 --> 00:49:51.459
Yeah.

00:49:51.459 --> 00:49:52.985
AUDIENCE: Thank you.

00:49:52.985 --> 00:49:54.610
JULIEN FINLAY: I'll
go to you, Antonio.

00:49:54.610 --> 00:49:56.272
But that's what you did as well.

00:49:56.272 --> 00:49:58.480
And I've read that on
[INAUDIBLE] blog, like a letter

00:49:58.480 --> 00:50:00.740
to your young self.

00:50:00.740 --> 00:50:02.290
Could you tell us
a bit more of this?

00:50:02.290 --> 00:50:07.290
And also, maybe I'm
wrong, but I know

00:50:07.290 --> 00:50:09.840
if you're within a smaller
community than the mainstream

00:50:09.840 --> 00:50:14.450
world, maybe going
online could be a refuge.

00:50:14.450 --> 00:50:18.779
So your younger self, would they
go online to have a safe haven?

00:50:18.779 --> 00:50:20.070
AOIFE MARTIN: Yeah, I think so.

00:50:20.070 --> 00:50:24.510
I mean, like for now, I wrote
a letter to my younger self.

00:50:24.510 --> 00:50:28.020
And basically, other
than buy shares in Apple,

00:50:28.020 --> 00:50:31.260
I told myself that
it was OK to be trans

00:50:31.260 --> 00:50:36.570
and that you will
get through this.

00:50:36.570 --> 00:50:38.640
I think when you're
that young and you

00:50:38.640 --> 00:50:39.780
know you're different
from everybody else,

00:50:39.780 --> 00:50:41.488
and you feel different
to everybody else,

00:50:41.488 --> 00:50:43.470
and there is no
representation out there,

00:50:43.470 --> 00:50:47.130
and you don't know anybody
else either in your peer group

00:50:47.130 --> 00:50:50.870
or on television or
anyone who is trans,

00:50:50.870 --> 00:50:52.680
and you never see
yourself represented,

00:50:52.680 --> 00:50:54.270
you think you're
the only person,

00:50:54.270 --> 00:50:58.249
and so just that, it was
just to myself, saying look,

00:50:58.249 --> 00:50:59.040
you will get there.

00:50:59.040 --> 00:51:00.960
You will come through this.

00:51:00.960 --> 00:51:02.880
And you will
eventually be happy.

00:51:02.880 --> 00:51:04.830
You will be an out trans woman.

00:51:04.830 --> 00:51:08.190
And you will speak about your
experiences of being trans.

00:51:08.190 --> 00:51:13.112
And I think if I'd had the
internet in those days,

00:51:13.112 --> 00:51:14.820
then I think, yeah,
I probably would have

00:51:14.820 --> 00:51:16.480
come out a lot sooner, I think.

00:51:16.480 --> 00:51:18.830
And I know in the
early days of internet,

00:51:18.830 --> 00:51:21.939
there was a lot of stuff
out there which we probably

00:51:21.939 --> 00:51:23.730
shouldn't be viewing
at that age, you know?

00:51:23.730 --> 00:51:28.896
And certainly, I think it
was difficult initially.

00:51:28.896 --> 00:51:30.770
Even when I first started
using the internet,

00:51:30.770 --> 00:51:34.770
there were very few
communities out there.

00:51:34.770 --> 00:51:37.610
I think social media
has improved enormously.

00:51:37.610 --> 00:51:39.327
And yeah, I
definitely would have

00:51:39.327 --> 00:51:41.160
be online and definitely
would have probably

00:51:41.160 --> 00:51:42.326
come out a lot sooner, yeah.

00:51:42.770 --> 00:51:43.860
JULIEN FINLAY: All right.

00:51:43.860 --> 00:51:44.369
Go ahead.

00:51:44.369 --> 00:51:44.910
AUDIENCE: Hi.

00:51:44.910 --> 00:51:46.390
My name is Antonio.

00:51:46.390 --> 00:51:48.660
My question is more for Finlay.

00:51:48.660 --> 00:51:51.410
You kind of mentioned
that in your video,

00:51:51.410 --> 00:51:55.560
the men-to-men action
started or contributed

00:51:55.560 --> 00:52:00.360
to the hate or the backlash.

00:52:00.360 --> 00:52:04.320
I don't know if you know the
Kilted Coaches or the Coaches

00:52:04.320 --> 00:52:05.357
Kilted from Scotland.

00:52:05.357 --> 00:52:06.190
FINLAY WILSON: Yeah.

00:52:06.190 --> 00:52:07.430
They live down the road.

00:52:07.430 --> 00:52:10.010
[LAUGHTER]

00:52:10.010 --> 00:52:11.910
AUDIENCE: So I wanted
to know if you know

00:52:11.910 --> 00:52:14.280
or if you know the story, if
something happened to them,

00:52:14.280 --> 00:52:15.810
they had the same backlash.

00:52:15.810 --> 00:52:17.820
I don't think they
identify themselves as gay.

00:52:17.820 --> 00:52:20.495
But they have a lot of
men-to-men action in a kilt.

00:52:20.495 --> 00:52:21.870
FINLAY WILSON:
They have actually

00:52:21.870 --> 00:52:25.620
spoken really publicly about--

00:52:25.620 --> 00:52:29.160
if you are watching, guys,
we've spoken about this.

00:52:29.160 --> 00:52:30.810
So actually, we
spoke about it live.

00:52:30.810 --> 00:52:35.420
And they have addressed it
to their fans quite a lot.

00:52:35.420 --> 00:52:37.160
But obviously,
they're both straight.

00:52:37.160 --> 00:52:38.632
They have their wives.

00:52:38.632 --> 00:52:39.590
They've got their kids.

00:52:39.590 --> 00:52:41.460
They're very open about that.

00:52:41.460 --> 00:52:45.240
But they're also
happy to play to--

00:52:45.240 --> 00:52:47.860
what do we call it,
like the Pink Pound--

00:52:47.860 --> 00:52:49.840
to work that.

00:52:49.840 --> 00:52:53.930
But when I did it, people
were uncomfortable,

00:52:53.930 --> 00:52:54.800
because they knew.

00:52:54.800 --> 00:52:57.125
By that point, I'd already
produced-- the hate

00:52:57.125 --> 00:52:58.250
letter had already come in.

00:52:58.250 --> 00:52:59.920
I'd already produced the video.

00:52:59.920 --> 00:53:01.810
I mean, like, this
is terrible, blah.

00:53:01.810 --> 00:53:03.350
I'd already being seen as that.

00:53:03.350 --> 00:53:06.010
And so video number two,
the people are like, maybe

00:53:06.010 --> 00:53:07.010
these are straight guys.

00:53:07.010 --> 00:53:09.470
Maybe we'll find straight
guys in the woods.

00:53:09.470 --> 00:53:12.680
Suddenly, it was like, no,
it's a faggot in the woods.

00:53:12.680 --> 00:53:15.860
And that was a huge
shift to see that.

00:53:15.860 --> 00:53:17.160
They knew.

00:53:17.160 --> 00:53:19.070
And they were uncomfortable.

00:53:19.070 --> 00:53:22.250
And it was a really
big change to see that.

00:53:22.250 --> 00:53:25.360
And the languaging really
changed in that regard.

00:53:25.360 --> 00:53:26.120
Yeah.

00:53:26.120 --> 00:53:29.226
And that's from that
piece of information.

00:53:29.226 --> 00:53:31.929
Yeah.

00:53:31.929 --> 00:53:32.470
AUDIENCE: Hi.

00:53:32.470 --> 00:53:33.190
I'm Rina.

00:53:33.190 --> 00:53:34.150
And I have a question.

00:53:34.150 --> 00:53:38.140
If you ever talk to
the haters and ask,

00:53:38.140 --> 00:53:40.060
what actually are you afraid of?

00:53:42.650 --> 00:53:45.680
FINLAY WILSON: This is
almost a misunderstanding

00:53:45.680 --> 00:53:49.640
that homophobia means
that they're scared.

00:53:49.640 --> 00:53:51.920
They're not usually
scared of us at all.

00:53:56.644 --> 00:53:58.810
I think everybody in this
room has had conversations

00:53:58.810 --> 00:54:00.850
with people where you
have had disagreements.

00:54:00.850 --> 00:54:03.220
And you're never going
to meet eye to eye.

00:54:03.220 --> 00:54:05.830
I've never had one of
those celebrity turnaround

00:54:05.830 --> 00:54:08.380
moments, where when you've
like spoken to a hater,

00:54:08.380 --> 00:54:09.310
and they've been
like, oh, actually

00:54:09.310 --> 00:54:10.180
I'm just really hurting.

00:54:10.180 --> 00:54:11.471
And let me tell you this thing.

00:54:11.471 --> 00:54:13.069
That doesn't happen
to me, all right?

00:54:13.069 --> 00:54:14.110
That hasn't happen to me.

00:54:14.110 --> 00:54:16.390
They just spew their venom.

00:54:16.390 --> 00:54:17.950
And at some point,
I have to say,

00:54:17.950 --> 00:54:21.490
I cannot attend
this arena anymore.

00:54:21.490 --> 00:54:22.440
I'm done here.

00:54:22.440 --> 00:54:23.880
I gave you a moment.

00:54:23.880 --> 00:54:25.290
I tried.

00:54:25.290 --> 00:54:26.839
But I can't.

00:54:26.839 --> 00:54:29.130
I've never had one of those
breakthrough moments, where

00:54:29.130 --> 00:54:30.360
it's like, we're going
to have a crowdfunder

00:54:30.360 --> 00:54:31.840
campaign for their surgery.

00:54:31.840 --> 00:54:35.217
I've not had that
at all, you know?

00:54:35.217 --> 00:54:36.550
You know kind of the one I mean?

00:54:36.550 --> 00:54:39.490
Like was it Sarah Silverman
did that against her hater?

00:54:39.490 --> 00:54:42.210
And it was lovely, lovely thing.

00:54:42.210 --> 00:54:45.582
That's a very romanticized thing
about online hate, I think.

00:54:45.582 --> 00:54:47.790
JULIEN FINLAY: Would that
be the same for you, Aoife,

00:54:47.790 --> 00:54:49.470
like you would not--

00:54:49.470 --> 00:54:50.100
I don't know.

00:54:50.100 --> 00:54:51.850
The potential of hate
would prevent you

00:54:51.850 --> 00:54:56.520
of engaging online with
your haters or your least

00:54:56.520 --> 00:54:57.690
appreciated fans?

00:54:57.690 --> 00:54:59.523
AOIFE MARTIN: So somewhat
similar to Finlay,

00:54:59.523 --> 00:55:03.020
I think I'm generally-- when
I first started coming out

00:55:03.020 --> 00:55:06.500
and was quite outspoken about
being trans, I was very open

00:55:06.500 --> 00:55:08.430
and would answer
people's questions.

00:55:08.430 --> 00:55:10.770
You know, because you want
to sort of educate people.

00:55:10.770 --> 00:55:11.380
FINLAY WILSON:
Yeah, information.

00:55:11.380 --> 00:55:12.870
AOIFE MARTIN: It's information.

00:55:12.870 --> 00:55:16.920
But the older I get, the
more cynical I get about it.

00:55:19.810 --> 00:55:23.490
And I think I'm very quick
now at spotting when somebody

00:55:23.490 --> 00:55:25.410
is being genuine and
somebody is just asking,

00:55:25.410 --> 00:55:26.868
trying to catch me
out on something

00:55:26.868 --> 00:55:28.380
and use it against me.

00:55:28.380 --> 00:55:31.260
And I'm very, very quick
to sort of just block

00:55:31.260 --> 00:55:34.350
people on Twitter.

00:55:34.350 --> 00:55:35.850
My life is not a debate.

00:55:35.850 --> 00:55:40.650
You can't sit there and demand
why I should get rights.

00:55:40.650 --> 00:55:42.650
I should have the rights.

00:55:42.650 --> 00:55:44.842
That's the basic
bottom line here.

00:55:44.842 --> 00:55:45.800
FINLAY WILSON: Exactly.

00:55:45.800 --> 00:55:46.591
AOIFE MARTIN: Yeah.

00:55:46.591 --> 00:55:48.594
And so I just don't
engage with it anymore.

00:55:48.594 --> 00:55:50.760
Because like you say, you
cannot change their minds.

00:55:50.760 --> 00:55:52.800
There is no wonderful
moment where

00:55:52.800 --> 00:55:54.030
people go, oh, you're right.

00:55:54.030 --> 00:55:55.411
And I'm going to change my ways.

00:55:55.411 --> 00:55:56.160
It doesn't happen.

00:55:56.160 --> 00:55:56.820
FINLAY WILSON: I
think a lot of people

00:55:56.820 --> 00:55:59.690
also think that trolls are
looking for engagement,

00:55:59.690 --> 00:56:01.470
that not necessarily.

00:56:01.470 --> 00:56:04.290
I mean, when I did the
video about mental health,

00:56:04.290 --> 00:56:06.702
one of the first
five comments was,

00:56:06.702 --> 00:56:08.910
you should have followed
through on killing yourself.

00:56:12.930 --> 00:56:14.900
What do you do with that?

00:56:14.900 --> 00:56:16.400
What do you do with
how you interact

00:56:16.400 --> 00:56:19.899
with that person who's, in a
sentence, wished death on you?

00:56:19.899 --> 00:56:21.190
AOIFE MARTIN: That's the thing.

00:56:21.190 --> 00:56:24.900
I mean, 48% of young trans
kids have attempted suicide.

00:56:24.900 --> 00:56:28.040
And when this stat is
ever sort of produced

00:56:28.040 --> 00:56:30.380
and when I've mentioned
this online, people say,

00:56:30.380 --> 00:56:33.140
well, they're obviously
not trying hard enough.

00:56:33.140 --> 00:56:35.335
I mean, how do you deal
with that sort of hate?

00:56:35.335 --> 00:56:35.960
You just don't.

00:56:35.960 --> 00:56:37.250
You just go, sorry.

00:56:37.250 --> 00:56:38.080
JULIEN FINLAY: 48%?

00:56:38.080 --> 00:56:38.450
AOIFE MARTIN: Sorry?

00:56:38.450 --> 00:56:39.658
JULIEN FINLAY: 48%, you said?

00:56:39.658 --> 00:56:42.350
AOIFE MARTIN: 48%, yes, so
you just don't deal with.

00:56:42.350 --> 00:56:43.850
You cannot engage
with these people.

00:56:43.850 --> 00:56:45.660
There's just no point, you know?

00:56:45.660 --> 00:56:48.890
FINLAY WILSON: Yeah, like
the LGBT suicide rate

00:56:48.890 --> 00:56:54.850
is high, very high, much
higher in trans communities.

00:56:54.850 --> 00:57:01.470
And to see people writing
and wishing death on you

00:57:01.470 --> 00:57:03.120
is damaging.

00:57:03.120 --> 00:57:06.850
You can't help but question
not only their actions,

00:57:06.850 --> 00:57:09.330
but you begin to
question yourself.

00:57:09.330 --> 00:57:12.390
And remember, we were saying
earlier about that time

00:57:12.390 --> 00:57:12.960
to reflect.

00:57:12.960 --> 00:57:17.620
If somebody is questioning
your existence,

00:57:17.620 --> 00:57:19.380
has the troll had that?

00:57:19.380 --> 00:57:22.600
Has the troll genuinely
sat there and then

00:57:22.600 --> 00:57:25.480
reflected themselves on what
they have written and said,

00:57:25.480 --> 00:57:27.220
should I die?

00:57:27.220 --> 00:57:29.320
No, of course they haven't.

00:57:29.320 --> 00:57:30.850
But they will do it to us.

00:57:30.850 --> 00:57:31.720
JULIEN FINLAY: And
that's why it's sneaky.

00:57:31.720 --> 00:57:33.845
Because you would only see
the hate or the comments

00:57:33.845 --> 00:57:38.530
or the meme as something
online, not something

00:57:38.530 --> 00:57:43.140
that, well, boomerangs
physically in your face--

00:57:43.140 --> 00:57:44.640
to use another boomerang thing.

00:57:44.640 --> 00:57:49.300
But online hate does kill.

00:57:49.300 --> 00:57:51.330
You have young people
taking off their lives.

00:57:51.330 --> 00:57:53.530
You have people hiding
themselves, like you say,

00:57:53.530 --> 00:57:54.150
in house.

00:57:57.070 --> 00:57:59.080
And there's a lack of education.

00:57:59.080 --> 00:58:00.680
There's a lack of prevention.

00:58:00.680 --> 00:58:02.470
There's a lack of repression.

00:58:02.470 --> 00:58:04.930
But there's also beautiful
things, as you mentioned.

00:58:04.930 --> 00:58:06.810
There's also
creating a community.

00:58:06.810 --> 00:58:10.300
And there's also initiatives,
like an app called ReThink

00:58:10.300 --> 00:58:12.010
that I shared with you.

00:58:12.010 --> 00:58:14.690
So that app, which you
can download online--

00:58:14.690 --> 00:58:19.000
it's called ReThink-- it scans
your words that you're typing.

00:58:19.000 --> 00:58:22.880
And it allows you to post before
posting, basically telling you,

00:58:22.880 --> 00:58:23.380
hm.

00:58:23.380 --> 00:58:25.350
Are you sure you
want to do that now?

00:58:25.350 --> 00:58:29.230
And 93% of the 50,000
users have decided

00:58:29.230 --> 00:58:30.970
not to post the
message they were

00:58:30.970 --> 00:58:34.720
writing in the first place.

00:58:34.720 --> 00:58:38.580
To what extent do you think
technology can educate them,

00:58:38.580 --> 00:58:39.550
educate those haters?

00:58:39.550 --> 00:58:43.649
Or is it just a battle
we will never fight?

00:58:43.649 --> 00:58:45.440
It will have been black
people in the past.

00:58:45.440 --> 00:58:46.398
It will have been gays.

00:58:46.398 --> 00:58:47.170
And it is trans.

00:58:47.170 --> 00:58:49.000
It will be something
else I'm against.

00:58:49.000 --> 00:58:51.000
I have a lot of hate.

00:58:51.000 --> 00:58:52.400
But what do you feel about that?

00:58:52.400 --> 00:58:53.191
AOIFE MARTIN: Yeah.

00:58:53.191 --> 00:58:56.420
I mean, see, I think when
people write hateful stuff,

00:58:56.420 --> 00:58:59.830
they're not seeing the person
on the other side of the screen.

00:58:59.830 --> 00:59:03.010
So there is no sort of concept
of a human being there.

00:59:03.010 --> 00:59:04.960
And so it's easy to write stuff.

00:59:04.960 --> 00:59:07.240
It's easy to write stuff
that you wouldn't say face

00:59:07.240 --> 00:59:09.220
to face to somebody.

00:59:09.220 --> 00:59:14.800
And I would never tweet
in anger or would never

00:59:14.800 --> 00:59:16.407
write an email in
anger, because you

00:59:16.407 --> 00:59:18.240
know you're going to
regret it the next day.

00:59:18.240 --> 00:59:20.706
FINLAY WILSON: You a
better person than me.

00:59:20.706 --> 00:59:21.532
[LAUGHS]

00:59:21.532 --> 00:59:23.990
AOIFE MARTIN: You just know
you're going to regret someday.

00:59:23.990 --> 00:59:31.180
And I think that having an
app that sort of captures

00:59:31.180 --> 00:59:34.330
that, I don't know
if it works or not.

00:59:34.330 --> 00:59:36.190
I mean, I would
hope people would

00:59:36.190 --> 00:59:39.250
have enough
self-perception to realize

00:59:39.250 --> 00:59:41.440
to know what they're doing.

00:59:41.440 --> 00:59:42.980
But obviously, that
isn't the case.

00:59:42.980 --> 00:59:44.800
JULIEN FINLAY: Finlay, before
I conclude and really open

00:59:44.800 --> 00:59:46.690
the conversation
and before you tell

00:59:46.690 --> 00:59:50.170
us more about your full hatred
emails that you regret--

00:59:50.170 --> 00:59:52.170
FINLAY WILSON: It mostly
involved my ex-husband.

00:59:52.170 --> 00:59:53.609
But that's a different thing.

00:59:53.609 --> 00:59:54.650
JULIEN FINLAY: Oh, juicy.

00:59:58.500 --> 01:00:00.350
Same topic-- would you be aware?

01:00:00.350 --> 01:00:03.345
Or would you know any ways
technology can somehow--

01:00:03.345 --> 01:00:04.970
FINLAY WILSON: I find
that interesting.

01:00:04.970 --> 01:00:07.220
Obviously, the user would
have to consent to its use.

01:00:07.220 --> 01:00:09.136
This is the thing about
policing the internet.

01:00:09.136 --> 01:00:12.620
We can't have that
going out for everybody.

01:00:12.620 --> 01:00:14.300
But to give people
that moment of pause,

01:00:14.300 --> 01:00:17.795
where the perhaps
taught hateful impulse

01:00:17.795 --> 01:00:20.390
is the first thing
that is there.

01:00:20.390 --> 01:00:23.060
Maybe that small pause is
enough of a window for empathy

01:00:23.060 --> 01:00:24.410
to come in.

01:00:24.410 --> 01:00:30.990
But empathy is that big part.

01:00:30.990 --> 01:00:35.040
You almost cannot exist now
and not know somebody-- well,

01:00:35.040 --> 01:00:36.180
maybe--

01:00:36.180 --> 01:00:39.480
not know somebody
that is gay, trans.

01:00:39.480 --> 01:00:40.820
You will know someone.

01:00:40.820 --> 01:00:42.810
There will be someone
in your family

01:00:42.810 --> 01:00:47.230
that you can look at and
acknowledge their humanity, so

01:00:47.230 --> 01:00:51.350
much so, to the point that when
we teach our yoga teachers,

01:00:51.350 --> 01:00:52.150
it's like, OK.

01:00:52.150 --> 01:00:54.010
You need to remember you're
working with humans, not just

01:00:54.010 --> 01:00:55.640
machines and make
them do X, Y, and Z.

01:00:55.640 --> 01:00:58.030
So we make them sit and look
each other, uninterrupted,

01:00:58.030 --> 01:01:01.390
in their eyes for like minutes.

01:01:01.390 --> 01:01:03.070
It's really uncomfortable.

01:01:03.070 --> 01:01:12.430
But they usually end up seeing
mirrored what they are seeing.

01:01:12.430 --> 01:01:14.930
So they will soften.

01:01:14.930 --> 01:01:16.430
And so even though
they may have had

01:01:16.430 --> 01:01:17.888
some animosity
towards that person,

01:01:17.888 --> 01:01:19.340
they will see a kinship.

01:01:19.340 --> 01:01:22.200
They can't get
that from a screen.

01:01:22.200 --> 01:01:23.010
They see something.

01:01:23.010 --> 01:01:25.200
There might be some
other insidious thing,

01:01:25.200 --> 01:01:26.004
like a jealousy.

01:01:26.004 --> 01:01:27.170
There might be a bitterness.

01:01:27.170 --> 01:01:29.269
There might be some other
story that comes in.

01:01:29.269 --> 01:01:30.810
And they forget that
the other person

01:01:30.810 --> 01:01:34.610
has just as unique and valid
a story as anybody else.

01:01:34.610 --> 01:01:37.810
And the screen is the barrier.

01:01:37.810 --> 01:01:39.760
In person, it's
very unusual for me

01:01:39.760 --> 01:01:43.160
to have somebody spout
venom to my face.

01:01:43.160 --> 01:01:47.730
It's more it will always be
hating behind the screen.

01:01:47.730 --> 01:01:51.470
JULIEN FINLAY: Let's have
all your questions heard.

01:01:51.470 --> 01:01:54.815
Oh, thanks, [INAUDIBLE].

01:01:54.815 --> 01:01:55.315
[LAUGHTER]

01:01:55.315 --> 01:01:57.231
FINLAY WILSON: You
have to do the work.

01:01:57.231 --> 01:01:59.626
[LAUGHTER]

01:02:01.176 --> 01:02:02.050
AUDIENCE: Is this on?

01:02:02.050 --> 01:02:03.244
This is on.

01:02:03.244 --> 01:02:04.910
Thank you so much for
talking so openly.

01:02:04.910 --> 01:02:06.630
I wanted to ask about--

01:02:06.630 --> 01:02:11.090
you spoke a little about how
harassment online and hate

01:02:11.090 --> 01:02:17.210
online will lead you to police
or regulate your online posts

01:02:17.210 --> 01:02:19.640
and self-expression online.

01:02:19.640 --> 01:02:22.140
You spoke a little about
how you set your self

01:02:22.140 --> 01:02:25.460
doubt even before you
step out the door, even.

01:02:25.460 --> 01:02:28.190
I guess I just wanted to
ask more broadly about how

01:02:28.190 --> 01:02:31.640
being online in general and
being influential online

01:02:31.640 --> 01:02:34.414
has maybe caused you to regulate
or police or expression.

01:02:34.414 --> 01:02:36.080
You mentioned a little
bit earlier about

01:02:36.080 --> 01:02:39.240
how there's a studio you're
aware of who replicate

01:02:39.240 --> 01:02:40.706
your poses on a frequent basis.

01:02:40.706 --> 01:02:42.080
And so you're
mindful of how they

01:02:42.080 --> 01:02:46.220
might perceive you responding
negatively to online hate.

01:02:46.220 --> 01:02:47.630
And so I wonder in general how--

01:02:47.630 --> 01:02:50.450
not cyberbullying, but
I guess cyber-validation

01:02:50.450 --> 01:02:52.970
or cyber-fandom has
maybe caused you

01:02:52.970 --> 01:02:58.530
to regulate or police or alter
your online self-expression,

01:02:58.530 --> 01:03:00.440
or even offline?

01:03:00.440 --> 01:03:02.660
JULIEN FINLAY: Aoife, do
you want to take that first?

01:03:02.660 --> 01:03:03.451
AOIFE MARTIN: Yeah.

01:03:03.451 --> 01:03:11.120
So I don't think it's affected
me too much in that sense.

01:03:11.120 --> 01:03:13.389
I'm quite outspoken
about what I talk about.

01:03:13.389 --> 01:03:14.930
I'm quite outspoken
about, obviously,

01:03:14.930 --> 01:03:16.829
about trans rights
is probably primarily

01:03:16.829 --> 01:03:17.870
what I talk about online.

01:03:17.870 --> 01:03:19.460
And I'm sure people
are going, oh, god.

01:03:19.460 --> 01:03:21.050
There she goes again,
off on one of her rants

01:03:21.050 --> 01:03:22.000
in one of her threads.

01:03:22.000 --> 01:03:25.110
And so I'm more sort of
self-conscious sometimes

01:03:25.110 --> 01:03:25.610
about it.

01:03:25.610 --> 01:03:26.780
I'm going, oh, do
people actually

01:03:26.780 --> 01:03:27.860
want to listen to this again?

01:03:27.860 --> 01:03:29.540
Do people want to hear
this sort of stuff again?

01:03:29.540 --> 01:03:31.040
Because I know I
tweet about it a lot.

01:03:31.040 --> 01:03:32.150
And I talk about it a lot.

01:03:32.150 --> 01:03:33.816
And I'm going, are
people going to think

01:03:33.816 --> 01:03:35.420
I'm being a little
bit narcissistic

01:03:35.420 --> 01:03:37.117
about this and with that?

01:03:37.117 --> 01:03:39.450
So I think that's more of how
I sort of regulate myself.

01:03:39.450 --> 01:03:43.250
I don't do as many long posts
or threads as I used to do.

01:03:43.250 --> 01:03:46.670
Because I think I have the
same bunch of followers.

01:03:46.670 --> 01:03:48.420
And they're obviously
aware of my politics

01:03:48.420 --> 01:03:49.836
and aware of where
I'm coming from

01:03:49.836 --> 01:03:52.490
and aware of what I talk about.

01:03:52.490 --> 01:03:56.270
And so yeah, I think it's
more I'm much more self-aware

01:03:56.270 --> 01:03:57.020
than I used to be.

01:03:57.020 --> 01:04:01.264
I'm much more afraid that
I'm actually boring people

01:04:01.264 --> 01:04:02.430
with my stuff now, you know?

01:04:02.430 --> 01:04:07.710
So generally, I hold back
a little because of that.

01:04:07.710 --> 01:04:10.516
But I had a thread
this week, because it's

01:04:10.516 --> 01:04:11.390
Trans Awareness Week.

01:04:11.390 --> 01:04:14.870
And sometimes if the muse
just strikes, I'll just go.

01:04:14.870 --> 01:04:16.100
And I'll write away.

01:04:16.100 --> 01:04:18.294
And I'll just post what
I'm thinking, so post first

01:04:18.294 --> 01:04:20.210
and then regret later
sort of thing, you know?

01:04:23.090 --> 01:04:24.800
FINLAY WILSON: I mean,
certainly for me,

01:04:24.800 --> 01:04:26.330
Instagram is my main platform.

01:04:26.330 --> 01:04:29.540
It's been where it's
always been a journal

01:04:29.540 --> 01:04:32.460
of my practice, my yoga practice
and kind of what's going on,

01:04:32.460 --> 01:04:33.650
day to day.

01:04:33.650 --> 01:04:38.340
So that part continues.

01:04:38.340 --> 01:04:41.520
I use it to catalog some of
the work breakthroughs I have.

01:04:41.520 --> 01:04:44.400
But those things
that happen there,

01:04:44.400 --> 01:04:47.040
they don't make it into
my classroom environment.

01:04:47.040 --> 01:04:48.120
I'm just more aware--

01:04:48.120 --> 01:04:52.970
that example of there's
a class that looks at it.

01:04:52.970 --> 01:04:55.400
They are probably
looking at the poses,

01:04:55.400 --> 01:04:59.900
because they are six,
six or seven years old.

01:04:59.900 --> 01:05:01.940
So they're unlikely to
be reading the politics

01:05:01.940 --> 01:05:04.400
or me rambling on at somebody.

01:05:04.400 --> 01:05:08.494
But it still is a thought
that they are looking at it.

01:05:08.494 --> 01:05:13.670
But I still stand by and have
always stood by, in person,

01:05:13.670 --> 01:05:17.000
if I see somebody going after me
or going after somebody that I

01:05:17.000 --> 01:05:19.007
care about, I'm going
to speak up about it.

01:05:19.007 --> 01:05:20.840
If that's happening,
I'll speak up about it.

01:05:20.840 --> 01:05:22.214
Even when I was
at high school, I

01:05:22.214 --> 01:05:25.700
set up this anti-bullying
network in my school.

01:05:25.700 --> 01:05:29.180
So that bit has been there.

01:05:29.180 --> 01:05:34.850
As for the online, the
online stuff for me,

01:05:34.850 --> 01:05:35.840
that's not fabricated.

01:05:35.840 --> 01:05:36.677
That's my every day.

01:05:36.677 --> 01:05:39.260
That's why the floor looks dirty
and the windows aren't clean.

01:05:39.260 --> 01:05:40.760
Yesterday, I
accidentally showed you

01:05:40.760 --> 01:05:42.710
a video of the toilet
because I forgot

01:05:42.710 --> 01:05:44.090
to shut the bathroom door.

01:05:44.090 --> 01:05:45.620
So I like to think
that I'm being

01:05:45.620 --> 01:05:47.640
as transparent as possible.

01:05:47.640 --> 01:05:49.700
And even though some of
my posts are generated

01:05:49.700 --> 01:05:55.220
in a reactionary way,
it's still my genuine take

01:05:55.220 --> 01:05:56.150
on the situation.

01:05:56.150 --> 01:06:00.420
So I'm still able
to, even though--

01:06:00.420 --> 01:06:04.220
has it become a
validation anymore?

01:06:04.220 --> 01:06:07.780
I think it's more like I
feel more appreciated when

01:06:07.780 --> 01:06:10.060
the voice feels heard,
and especially when

01:06:10.060 --> 01:06:12.550
I hear the rally cry go
out, when people are like,

01:06:12.550 --> 01:06:14.350
this has happened to me as well.

01:06:14.350 --> 01:06:15.940
And that's powerful.

01:06:15.940 --> 01:06:18.440
Because the young
me didn't have that.

01:06:18.440 --> 01:06:22.270
The young me was so
isolated, even when

01:06:22.270 --> 01:06:24.610
I was starting to
come out, there

01:06:24.610 --> 01:06:27.445
were events and things happening
there that were so destructive.

01:06:27.445 --> 01:06:30.040
There were things that happened
when I was way young that

01:06:30.040 --> 01:06:30.920
were so destructive.

01:06:30.920 --> 01:06:34.330
Actually, I've even tried to
speak to my partner about it

01:06:34.330 --> 01:06:34.930
face-to-face.

01:06:34.930 --> 01:06:38.650
He said, I can never understand
what you went through.

01:06:38.650 --> 01:06:39.550
And that's it.

01:06:39.550 --> 01:06:42.040
And even though he may not
mean to put a wall there,

01:06:42.040 --> 01:06:43.709
there's a solid wall there.

01:06:43.709 --> 01:06:46.000
So for example, you speak to
someone about child abuse.

01:06:46.000 --> 01:06:48.940
And their hackles are up.

01:06:48.940 --> 01:06:52.810
But if I write about that,
it's like a pebble in a pond.

01:06:52.810 --> 01:06:54.102
And the ripples will reach out.

01:06:54.102 --> 01:06:56.601
And some of the other people
that have been affected by that

01:06:56.601 --> 01:06:58.920
will actually gather together
and feel heartened by it.

01:06:58.920 --> 01:07:01.990
And actually, I
feel like that's--

01:07:01.990 --> 01:07:05.290
I would never think putting
a sexual abuse story online

01:07:05.290 --> 01:07:07.720
is looking for validation.

01:07:07.720 --> 01:07:13.066
But it is looking for an outlet
to put the emotion to paper,

01:07:13.066 --> 01:07:14.190
usually for the first time.

01:07:14.190 --> 01:07:15.170
So usually when I'm
writing, I'm not

01:07:15.170 --> 01:07:17.360
writing there on my
computer, or being like,

01:07:17.360 --> 01:07:18.530
let's see how long--

01:07:18.530 --> 01:07:19.640
let's edit this.

01:07:19.640 --> 01:07:22.610
It's just coming out of my head.

01:07:22.610 --> 01:07:24.650
And very rarely do
I edit unless I've

01:07:24.650 --> 01:07:27.170
had like an absolute
autocorrect error.

01:07:27.170 --> 01:07:31.020
But it's as direct
as I can make it.

01:07:31.020 --> 01:07:32.270
Some of it may be reactionary.

01:07:32.270 --> 01:07:34.520
But I'm not policing it too
much, if that makes sense.

01:07:34.520 --> 01:07:36.987
I'm trying to be as
genuine as possible.

01:07:36.987 --> 01:07:38.070
And I try to dumb it down.

01:07:38.070 --> 01:07:41.580
Because my yoga classes, I am--

01:07:41.580 --> 01:07:42.524
well, it's a show.

01:07:42.524 --> 01:07:43.440
Let's put it that way.

01:07:43.440 --> 01:07:44.400
It's a show.

01:07:44.400 --> 01:07:45.441
JULIEN FINLAY: All right.

01:07:45.441 --> 01:07:46.820
We're all going at 4:00 PM.

01:07:46.820 --> 01:07:49.028
AOIFE MARTIN: Yeah, I think
that's a very good point.

01:07:49.028 --> 01:07:50.824
I mean, there are
some subjects I'm

01:07:50.824 --> 01:07:51.990
uncomfortable talking about.

01:07:51.990 --> 01:07:53.890
Because I don't know
how to express myself.

01:07:53.890 --> 01:07:56.319
And it's certainly
around gender dysphoria,

01:07:56.319 --> 01:07:58.360
but the feelings of
dysphoria and what it's like.

01:07:58.360 --> 01:07:59.943
Because it's very
hard to explain that

01:07:59.943 --> 01:08:02.100
to somebody who isn't trans.

01:08:02.100 --> 01:08:06.250
And I do write bits and pieces
about it when I can or when--

01:08:06.250 --> 01:08:09.150
and it does, as you said,
those ripples, they go out.

01:08:09.150 --> 01:08:09.880
People see it.

01:08:09.880 --> 01:08:11.730
People who are going
through the same thing

01:08:11.730 --> 01:08:13.630
will take some sort of
validation from that.

01:08:13.630 --> 01:08:16.410
And they go, well, I'm not the
only one who feels like that.

01:08:16.410 --> 01:08:17.920
And it's nice to get that.

01:08:17.920 --> 01:08:20.679
And when I see people
writing about dysphoria,

01:08:20.679 --> 01:08:23.880
well, yeah, I see that
describes perfectly how I feel.

01:08:23.880 --> 01:08:25.080
You get it.

01:08:25.080 --> 01:08:28.439
Whereas, a lot of people
just don't understand it.

01:08:28.439 --> 01:08:31.260
And it's very hard for somebody
who hasn't experienced it

01:08:31.260 --> 01:08:32.702
to understand what it's like.

01:08:32.702 --> 01:08:34.410
FINLAY WILSON: I think
that was the power

01:08:34.410 --> 01:08:36.810
behind the Me Too movement.

01:08:36.810 --> 01:08:38.882
There are lots of
those movements that

01:08:38.882 --> 01:08:40.590
happened that didn't
get as much traction

01:08:40.590 --> 01:08:42.090
as the Me Too movement.

01:08:42.090 --> 01:08:44.899
But on the back of
that, actually, there

01:08:44.899 --> 01:08:49.660
were a lot of men, for example,
that also used the same tag

01:08:49.660 --> 01:08:52.790
and said, actually,
it's us as well.

01:08:52.790 --> 01:08:54.080
It's all of us.

01:08:54.080 --> 01:08:56.600
And so sometimes,
these social movements

01:08:56.600 --> 01:09:01.840
can be so positive, so powerful.

01:09:01.840 --> 01:09:03.580
But it does take
people to do it,

01:09:03.580 --> 01:09:07.180
to have that unaltered voice.

01:09:07.180 --> 01:09:07.786
Yeah.

01:09:07.786 --> 01:09:09.910
AOIFE MARTIN: Yeah, just
to know you're not alone--

01:09:09.910 --> 01:09:11.000
that's the main thing.

01:09:11.000 --> 01:09:11.985
You know you're not
the only person who

01:09:11.985 --> 01:09:12.901
have experienced this.

01:09:12.901 --> 01:09:13.939
You are not on your own.

01:09:13.939 --> 01:09:15.351
FINLAY WILSON: Yeah.

01:09:15.351 --> 01:09:16.850
JULIEN FINLAY: We
have two questions

01:09:16.850 --> 01:09:18.870
posted online internally.

01:09:18.870 --> 01:09:21.410
So it's policed and controlled.

01:09:21.410 --> 01:09:23.779
But then we can have more
questions from you all.

01:09:23.779 --> 01:09:24.830
FINLAY WILSON: Hopefully,
they took a minute

01:09:24.830 --> 01:09:26.080
to reflect on what they wrote.

01:09:26.080 --> 01:09:27.149
[LAUGHTER]

01:09:27.149 --> 01:09:29.569
JULIEN FINLAY: There's
one [INAUDIBLE]..

01:09:29.569 --> 01:09:32.390
The first one I have is--

01:09:32.390 --> 01:09:33.390
will be for both of you.

01:09:33.390 --> 01:09:36.680
So body positivity is
impacted by negativity

01:09:36.680 --> 01:09:39.130
from those around you.

01:09:39.130 --> 01:09:41.470
Like bullying, those
with weight issues

01:09:41.470 --> 01:09:45.550
are excluded and
treated, assumed lazy.

01:09:45.550 --> 01:09:48.069
Those who experience
this feel isolated

01:09:48.069 --> 01:09:50.529
and driving depression.

01:09:50.529 --> 01:09:53.609
How can, at Google--
but I would say,

01:09:53.609 --> 01:09:56.220
how can any tech companies--

01:09:56.220 --> 01:09:57.780
can we be truly inclusive?

01:09:57.780 --> 01:10:01.030
And can we see everyone
as a worthy person?

01:10:01.030 --> 01:10:02.550
That's a very good question.

01:10:02.550 --> 01:10:04.133
AOIFE MARTIN: That's
a great question.

01:10:04.133 --> 01:10:06.642
And I'm not sure
I can answer it.

01:10:06.642 --> 01:10:09.360
Body positivity, yeah,
that's a huge thing for me.

01:10:09.360 --> 01:10:12.610
It's something I
struggle with myself.

01:10:12.610 --> 01:10:16.440
And I, yeah, I'm a
middle-aged, fat, trans woman.

01:10:16.440 --> 01:10:20.040
And the word fat is something I
find it very difficult to say.

01:10:20.040 --> 01:10:22.042
I find it very
difficult to actually--

01:10:22.042 --> 01:10:24.417
that was probably the first
time I've used this publicly,

01:10:24.417 --> 01:10:27.630
to say that word, the
F word, as I call it.

01:10:27.630 --> 01:10:30.810
And yeah, it's something
I struggle with.

01:10:30.810 --> 01:10:32.350
I hate photographs of myself.

01:10:32.350 --> 01:10:34.890
I hate seeing pictures
of myself online.

01:10:34.890 --> 01:10:38.310
I do it because I'm trying
to be more positive about,

01:10:38.310 --> 01:10:39.130
this is me.

01:10:39.130 --> 01:10:40.860
This is what I look like.

01:10:40.860 --> 01:10:43.740
Accept it or walk away.

01:10:43.740 --> 01:10:45.470
But I still find it
very, very difficult.

01:10:45.470 --> 01:10:47.340
I've done a couple
of portrait sessions

01:10:47.340 --> 01:10:49.660
for some trans projects
that I'm involved in.

01:10:49.660 --> 01:10:53.310
And again, I'm
doing it because I'm

01:10:53.310 --> 01:10:56.850
trying to be more open about
who I am and be more positive

01:10:56.850 --> 01:10:58.142
and be more body positive.

01:10:58.142 --> 01:10:59.850
But I still find it
very, very difficult.

01:10:59.850 --> 01:11:02.391
And it's something I find very,
very difficult to talk about.

01:11:02.391 --> 01:11:04.950
And someday, I
probably will, I'll

01:11:04.950 --> 01:11:09.270
write a lot about
this when I get there.

01:11:09.270 --> 01:11:13.140
And I think it's
only by sort of--

01:11:13.140 --> 01:11:14.420
again, it's representation.

01:11:14.420 --> 01:11:19.020
It's showing different bodies,
different people, people

01:11:19.020 --> 01:11:22.710
of different color, gender,
sexualities, body shapes,

01:11:22.710 --> 01:11:25.110
body types.

01:11:25.110 --> 01:11:27.250
We are inundated with
images all the time

01:11:27.250 --> 01:11:30.810
of thin, white, blonde
people generally.

01:11:30.810 --> 01:11:33.920
And we need to get away
from that sort of thing.

01:11:33.920 --> 01:11:36.000
People's bodies are--
everybody's different.

01:11:36.000 --> 01:11:37.240
Not everybody is thin.

01:11:37.240 --> 01:11:38.676
Not everybody is tall.

01:11:38.676 --> 01:11:40.050
Not everybody is
white or blonde.

01:11:40.050 --> 01:11:41.880
So we need to--

01:11:41.880 --> 01:11:45.727
I think, yeah, we should
be promoting that.

01:11:45.727 --> 01:11:46.560
JULIEN FINLAY: Yeah.

01:11:46.560 --> 01:11:50.380
And we all have F words,
I guess, as demons.

01:11:50.380 --> 01:11:51.630
But thank you for saying this.

01:11:51.630 --> 01:11:52.950
And I'm sorry I asked
you for the picture now.

01:11:52.950 --> 01:11:53.490
I feel like--

01:11:53.490 --> 01:11:54.531
AOIFE MARTIN: Oh, no, no.

01:11:54.531 --> 01:11:57.930
That's actually-- that was done
in a photo booth at MasterCard.

01:11:57.930 --> 01:12:01.900
And that one's fine, because
it's only from chest up,

01:12:01.900 --> 01:12:02.970
which is grand.

01:12:02.970 --> 01:12:04.844
JULIEN FINLAY: Finlay,
I know body positivity

01:12:04.844 --> 01:12:09.990
is one of your main, well,
energy that is driving you.

01:12:09.990 --> 01:12:10.700
Tell us more.

01:12:10.700 --> 01:12:12.450
FINLAY WILSON: For me,
I don't necessarily

01:12:12.450 --> 01:12:15.720
see that as something that
someone else has responsibility

01:12:15.720 --> 01:12:16.470
for.

01:12:16.470 --> 01:12:19.140
When I have people coming
in, and they're coming in,

01:12:19.140 --> 01:12:21.360
and they have this
negative self-image,

01:12:21.360 --> 01:12:24.040
then my drive is to get
them to do the work.

01:12:24.040 --> 01:12:26.240
And that's the
work of acceptance.

01:12:26.240 --> 01:12:31.760
So part of yoga is
this shift of being

01:12:31.760 --> 01:12:33.760
more conscious about your
actions, how you move,

01:12:33.760 --> 01:12:37.897
but also practicing
acceptance of what is going on

01:12:37.897 --> 01:12:40.230
or what your current reality
is and what your powers are

01:12:40.230 --> 01:12:42.390
to change and affect things.

01:12:42.390 --> 01:12:45.360
So that process and
one of journaling

01:12:45.360 --> 01:12:47.490
and of introspection,
that begins

01:12:47.490 --> 01:12:52.900
the work of beginning to
care for the organism.

01:12:52.900 --> 01:12:56.110
And if you are willing to
do the work of the care,

01:12:56.110 --> 01:12:57.750
it doesn't matter how it looks.

01:12:57.750 --> 01:13:00.090
It doesn't matter
how the post looks.

01:13:00.090 --> 01:13:02.055
I work with people with
multiple disabilities.

01:13:02.055 --> 01:13:03.930
They're not looking on
the Instagram channels

01:13:03.930 --> 01:13:05.513
and being like, well,
I can't do that.

01:13:05.513 --> 01:13:07.980
They are interested in
creating a shape that

01:13:07.980 --> 01:13:09.920
will work for them.

01:13:09.920 --> 01:13:12.420
And they feel something
and feel steady in it.

01:13:12.420 --> 01:13:15.360
So yoga is great in this
adaptable way of teaching

01:13:15.360 --> 01:13:17.100
people the skills
to begin to practice

01:13:17.100 --> 01:13:18.900
acceptance of themselves.

01:13:18.900 --> 01:13:21.151
I and I think that's
where it needs to start.

01:13:21.151 --> 01:13:22.650
If it doesn't start
from there, then

01:13:22.650 --> 01:13:24.990
it is that external validation
from another to say,

01:13:24.990 --> 01:13:26.290
I need you to be OK with me.

01:13:26.290 --> 01:13:26.790
No.

01:13:26.790 --> 01:13:28.560
You need to be OK with you.

01:13:28.560 --> 01:13:30.060
If you're not OK
with you, then this

01:13:30.060 --> 01:13:32.809
is where it's all
going to go wrong.

01:13:32.809 --> 01:13:34.350
And this is where
the haters come in.

01:13:34.350 --> 01:13:36.750
And they make that
process harder.

01:13:36.750 --> 01:13:39.500
But on a daily basis, it
can be incredibly helpful.

01:13:39.500 --> 01:13:41.070
Now this is where
I'm going to get

01:13:41.070 --> 01:13:44.430
killed by the yoga community,
because not all yoga is created

01:13:44.430 --> 01:13:45.660
equal.

01:13:45.660 --> 01:13:49.260
My first yoga teacher
drove me to bulimia.

01:13:49.260 --> 01:13:51.000
Because she said,
you look this way.

01:13:51.000 --> 01:13:53.070
You've got this fat back here.

01:13:53.070 --> 01:13:56.880
I had like a 38-inch waist,
which I don't have now.

01:13:56.880 --> 01:14:00.160
And she was like, this bit
here, that pose, this twist,

01:14:00.160 --> 01:14:01.267
is not going to work.

01:14:01.267 --> 01:14:03.600
Let me teach you this ancient
cleansing technique, which

01:14:03.600 --> 01:14:05.160
was basically sticking your
finger down your throat

01:14:05.160 --> 01:14:07.920
and vomiting in a bucket, so
that I could lose the weight.

01:14:07.920 --> 01:14:09.460
And, oh, I lost the weight.

01:14:09.460 --> 01:14:10.630
I lost a lot of weight.

01:14:10.630 --> 01:14:12.430
I lost all my self-respect.

01:14:12.430 --> 01:14:14.490
I then started torturing
myself with food.

01:14:14.490 --> 01:14:16.170
Then I kind of
got into cleanses,

01:14:16.170 --> 01:14:17.760
where I would say,
oh, I'm detoxing,

01:14:17.760 --> 01:14:20.176
which basically was code for
I'm just drinking water today

01:14:20.176 --> 01:14:21.960
because I don't deserve to eat.

01:14:21.960 --> 01:14:25.021
And it really actually drove
me into this very dark place.

01:14:25.021 --> 01:14:26.520
And then actually,
the style of yoga

01:14:26.520 --> 01:14:30.430
that I teach now, the first
class of that that I went to,

01:14:30.430 --> 01:14:31.950
it was the very first moment.

01:14:31.950 --> 01:14:34.770
And I had already been teaching
yoga for about three years.

01:14:34.770 --> 01:14:37.220
I was still struggling
with an eating disorder.

01:14:37.220 --> 01:14:42.270
I was so part bulimic but was
also skipping meals and making

01:14:42.270 --> 01:14:45.450
it a health choice,
was skipping meals,

01:14:45.450 --> 01:14:49.020
was not in great
shape health-wise.

01:14:49.020 --> 01:14:50.270
And I went onto to this class.

01:14:50.270 --> 01:14:52.360
It was the first time
ever in a yoga class

01:14:52.360 --> 01:14:57.600
that an instructor had
asked me to feel how I felt.

01:14:57.600 --> 01:14:59.590
And it was just like,
take a deep breath.

01:14:59.590 --> 01:15:02.722
Feel somewhere in your body that
is sore and needs attention.

01:15:02.722 --> 01:15:03.930
I had never done that before.

01:15:03.930 --> 01:15:05.670
I was like, what
the fuck is this?

01:15:05.670 --> 01:15:08.200
Who is this hippy?

01:15:08.200 --> 01:15:09.490
And--

01:15:09.490 --> 01:15:12.400
JULIEN FINLAY: Says the guy
wearing a kilt with a beard.

01:15:12.400 --> 01:15:14.680
FINLAY WILSON: Do not
call me a hipster, sir,

01:15:14.680 --> 01:15:16.090
despite all of this.

01:15:16.090 --> 01:15:19.996
So by the end of that class--

01:15:19.996 --> 01:15:22.120
it was a two-hour class--
by the end of that class,

01:15:22.120 --> 01:15:23.350
I was sitting there,
shell-shocked.

01:15:23.350 --> 01:15:25.474
Because I had invested a
lot of my energy and stuff

01:15:25.474 --> 01:15:26.090
in my career.

01:15:26.090 --> 01:15:27.756
And I was like, I'm
a good yoga teacher.

01:15:27.756 --> 01:15:29.660
I am totally at top of my game.

01:15:29.660 --> 01:15:32.320
And after that class,
I felt that everything

01:15:32.320 --> 01:15:35.290
I had learned-- this is after
one class-- everything was

01:15:35.290 --> 01:15:39.180
a deception and that I had
to face up to in that moment

01:15:39.180 --> 01:15:42.690
that I had been damaging
myself and calling it healing.

01:15:42.690 --> 01:15:45.431
And that was a real gear shift.

01:15:45.431 --> 01:15:46.930
And so that was
when I started doing

01:15:46.930 --> 01:15:48.520
the work of introspection.

01:15:48.520 --> 01:15:52.240
Because the work I'd been doing
before had been a distraction,

01:15:52.240 --> 01:15:53.740
which isn't the same.

01:15:53.740 --> 01:15:54.790
So I was doing the yoga.

01:15:54.790 --> 01:15:56.860
I was doing the
physical exercises.

01:15:56.860 --> 01:15:58.810
But I was using it
to punish my body.

01:15:58.810 --> 01:16:01.110
I wasn't using it to heal it.

01:16:01.110 --> 01:16:02.810
And it was only when
I made that shift

01:16:02.810 --> 01:16:04.870
and I really changed
styles of yoga

01:16:04.870 --> 01:16:07.810
that I was actually able
to really feel for that.

01:16:07.810 --> 01:16:09.509
And that was powerful.

01:16:09.509 --> 01:16:10.300
I did this process.

01:16:10.300 --> 01:16:12.597
It's called the shamanic death--

01:16:12.597 --> 01:16:13.180
very dramatic.

01:16:13.180 --> 01:16:14.680
I love drama.

01:16:14.680 --> 01:16:19.860
And you're led through this
visualization ceremony, where

01:16:19.860 --> 01:16:21.820
your last day on
earth is simulated,

01:16:21.820 --> 01:16:24.520
where you're made to write down
essentially a letter to all

01:16:24.520 --> 01:16:25.710
of your loved ones.

01:16:25.710 --> 01:16:28.240
You're made to look
at all the ways

01:16:28.240 --> 01:16:31.270
that you have wasted your
life, the things you've

01:16:31.270 --> 01:16:32.530
done to yourself.

01:16:32.530 --> 01:16:34.420
And then ceremonially, you die.

01:16:34.420 --> 01:16:36.640
You obviously don't die--

01:16:36.640 --> 01:16:37.630
spoiler.

01:16:37.630 --> 01:16:38.800
[LAUGHTER]

01:16:38.800 --> 01:16:41.530
You obviously don't die.

01:16:41.530 --> 01:16:44.380
But when you are
brought back, you

01:16:44.380 --> 01:16:47.352
are made to make these
affirmations of things

01:16:47.352 --> 01:16:48.560
that you will never do again.

01:16:48.560 --> 01:16:50.059
And from that moment,
the first time

01:16:50.059 --> 01:16:51.980
I did that process, that was it.

01:16:51.980 --> 01:16:54.960
The eating disorder stopped,
because I was able to identify.

01:16:54.960 --> 01:16:56.820
I was like, this is
ruining your life.

01:16:56.820 --> 01:17:00.080
This is making you
less than who you are.

01:17:00.080 --> 01:17:00.790
And that was it.

01:17:00.790 --> 01:17:02.084
It stopped.

01:17:02.084 --> 01:17:03.500
And it was at that
moment as well,

01:17:03.500 --> 01:17:05.060
where I was like,
there's a fight in you.

01:17:05.060 --> 01:17:06.140
And you need to bring it.

01:17:06.140 --> 01:17:08.514
And that's actually-- from
that moment was when I started

01:17:08.514 --> 01:17:09.850
thinking, I need to teach kids.

01:17:09.850 --> 01:17:11.951
I need to create a safe
space for children.

01:17:11.951 --> 01:17:14.450
I need to create a safe space
for children with disabilities

01:17:14.450 --> 01:17:15.080
and teach them.

01:17:15.080 --> 01:17:18.750
And when I teach them,
I am unashamedly me.

01:17:18.750 --> 01:17:19.292
They know me.

01:17:19.292 --> 01:17:21.250
They know that I'm going
to come in in the most

01:17:21.250 --> 01:17:22.200
outrageous leggings.

01:17:22.200 --> 01:17:24.270
And so will they.

01:17:24.270 --> 01:17:26.260
And I love that.

01:17:26.260 --> 01:17:28.300
JULIEN FINLAY: Accepting
yourself, and you said.

01:17:28.300 --> 01:17:28.880
All right.

01:17:28.880 --> 01:17:29.860
More questions, please.

01:17:32.444 --> 01:17:33.110
AUDIENCE: Sorry.

01:17:33.110 --> 01:17:34.810
I love the sound
of my own voice.

01:17:34.810 --> 01:17:36.060
JULIEN FINLAY: I love it, too.

01:17:36.060 --> 01:17:37.280
AUDIENCE: And this is
not even a question.

01:17:37.280 --> 01:17:38.540
It's just a comment.

01:17:38.540 --> 01:17:40.250
It's just about body positivity.

01:17:42.800 --> 01:17:44.679
We had a speaker
here from ShoutOut,

01:17:44.679 --> 01:17:46.220
this very important
Irish charity who

01:17:46.220 --> 01:17:47.930
do LGBT workshops in schools.

01:17:47.930 --> 01:17:50.150
And she had this very
interesting comment a year ago,

01:17:50.150 --> 01:17:52.370
where she said she came out
as bi when she was nine.

01:17:52.370 --> 01:17:54.620
But she came out
as fat in her 30s,

01:17:54.620 --> 01:17:59.870
and to realize that she's not
a thin woman in a fat woman's

01:17:59.870 --> 01:18:02.030
body, that this is who she is.

01:18:02.030 --> 01:18:04.790
And I think it was a very
important point about that body

01:18:04.790 --> 01:18:07.109
positivity often tends to
be about, oh, come here.

01:18:07.109 --> 01:18:08.150
You'll get there one day.

01:18:08.150 --> 01:18:11.720
We accept all body sizes
that diverge from the norm,

01:18:11.720 --> 01:18:14.000
implying there is a norm.

01:18:14.000 --> 01:18:15.230
And you know, we tolerate.

01:18:15.230 --> 01:18:17.188
But ideally, you should
work with someone else.

01:18:17.188 --> 01:18:19.700
And we all, many of us-- god
knows I did-- replicate this

01:18:19.700 --> 01:18:21.980
when we congratulate someone
when they lose weight,

01:18:21.980 --> 01:18:23.480
like, hey, well done.

01:18:23.480 --> 01:18:24.140
Good job.

01:18:24.140 --> 01:18:26.400
You're one step closer
to being normal.

01:18:26.400 --> 01:18:30.140
And so I guess I just wanted
to echoed that sentiment,

01:18:30.140 --> 01:18:31.280
that it's in all these--

01:18:31.280 --> 01:18:32.988
I don't want to call
it microaggressions.

01:18:32.988 --> 01:18:35.810
But I guess it's all in
these tiny, little steps we

01:18:35.810 --> 01:18:37.959
can take with each other
to just be more inclusive.

01:18:37.959 --> 01:18:38.750
AOIFE MARTIN: Yeah.

01:18:38.750 --> 01:18:39.450
I think that's great a point.

01:18:39.450 --> 01:18:41.324
I mean, actually, I met
with Bella this week.

01:18:41.324 --> 01:18:43.490
I actually had dinner
with her on Tuesday night.

01:18:43.490 --> 01:18:47.540
And she did mention
that to me as well,

01:18:47.540 --> 01:18:50.260
that of her sort of coming
out moment, not just

01:18:50.260 --> 01:18:52.370
as bi, but as a fat person.

01:18:52.370 --> 01:18:54.470
And I thought it was
wonderfully inspiring.

01:18:54.470 --> 01:18:57.470
So it's given me
food for thought--

01:18:57.470 --> 01:18:58.750
food being the operative word.

01:18:58.750 --> 01:19:03.210
And yeah, so I'm going
to certainly try and be

01:19:03.210 --> 01:19:05.150
a bit more body
positive about myself.

01:19:05.150 --> 01:19:06.800
Because this is who I am.

01:19:06.800 --> 01:19:10.794
And I don't see why I
should change just to--

01:19:10.794 --> 01:19:12.460
being trans is one
thing, because you're

01:19:12.460 --> 01:19:16.585
changing your body anyway,
with hormones and blockers.

01:19:16.585 --> 01:19:17.960
You can put on
two to three stone

01:19:17.960 --> 01:19:21.470
just by taking
estrogen, which isn't

01:19:21.470 --> 01:19:22.967
helping me get any thinner.

01:19:22.967 --> 01:19:24.800
So I just need to accept
who I am, you know,

01:19:24.800 --> 01:19:27.167
and just love
myself for how I am.

01:19:27.167 --> 01:19:29.000
JULIEN FINLAY: And you
beautiful as you are.

01:19:29.000 --> 01:19:31.215
And we are delighted
having beautiful panels.

01:19:31.215 --> 01:19:33.090
Do you want to add
something to that, Finlay,

01:19:33.090 --> 01:19:33.890
on body positivity?

01:19:33.890 --> 01:19:36.940
Have you already discussed?

01:19:36.940 --> 01:19:37.970
You don't have to.

01:19:37.970 --> 01:19:40.230
FINLAY WILSON: I
mean, certainly--

01:19:40.230 --> 01:19:46.317
I mean, in the yoga world, I
tell all of my students that

01:19:46.317 --> 01:19:48.650
buy yoga magazines-- this is
me not going to get my yoga

01:19:48.650 --> 01:19:50.829
magazine subscription
or paid from them--

01:19:50.829 --> 01:19:53.120
I say to them, it's like,
please stop buying this trash

01:19:53.120 --> 01:19:54.953
and actually donate
your money to a charity.

01:19:54.953 --> 01:19:56.790
That would be lovely.

01:19:56.790 --> 01:20:01.440
Because it is just
adverts of thin women

01:20:01.440 --> 01:20:02.535
selling yoga leggings.

01:20:02.535 --> 01:20:03.810
And that's all it is.

01:20:03.810 --> 01:20:04.960
It's all that it is.

01:20:04.960 --> 01:20:06.480
And those of you are like,
oh, no, it's more than that.

01:20:06.480 --> 01:20:07.740
It's women selling crystals.

01:20:07.740 --> 01:20:08.240
Yeah.

01:20:08.240 --> 01:20:09.310
[LAUGHTER]

01:20:09.310 --> 01:20:10.890
And the woman
selling the crystals

01:20:10.890 --> 01:20:13.900
is also thin and
blonde and perfect.

01:20:13.900 --> 01:20:15.240
So it's like, bah.

01:20:15.240 --> 01:20:17.550
But what I love is the
yoga studio that I teach

01:20:17.550 --> 01:20:21.800
at that I helped set
up, when the people,

01:20:21.800 --> 01:20:24.740
when everybody comes to
our studio, everybody

01:20:24.740 --> 01:20:27.350
who is anybody, they
come to the studio

01:20:27.350 --> 01:20:30.590
because they can do
the class regardless.

01:20:30.590 --> 01:20:32.300
It's not like, a, oh, come in.

01:20:32.300 --> 01:20:34.877
We'll help you lose the weight.

01:20:34.877 --> 01:20:36.960
That isn't the message
they get when they come in.

01:20:36.960 --> 01:20:38.010
It's like, come on in.

01:20:38.010 --> 01:20:40.930
We'll see what happens.

01:20:40.930 --> 01:20:43.180
JULIEN FINLAY: All right.

01:20:43.180 --> 01:20:46.270
Do you have any other questions,
anything that's on your mind?

01:20:46.270 --> 01:20:47.470
When is the next class?

01:20:50.080 --> 01:20:50.631
AUDIENCE: Hi.

01:20:50.631 --> 01:20:51.130
I'm Laura.

01:20:51.130 --> 01:20:56.775
And I have a question, because
I was active for animal rights

01:20:56.775 --> 01:20:57.400
some years ago.

01:20:57.400 --> 01:21:01.401
And I got a lot of hate from
online and from my friends

01:21:01.401 --> 01:21:01.900
as well.

01:21:01.900 --> 01:21:04.360
And especially, I
think if you get

01:21:04.360 --> 01:21:07.540
this hate from people
you like or your friends,

01:21:07.540 --> 01:21:09.700
it's a lot more hurtful.

01:21:09.700 --> 01:21:12.380
And I just wanted to know if
you dealt with this as well,

01:21:12.380 --> 01:21:14.230
and if you dealt with
it in a different way

01:21:14.230 --> 01:21:19.900
than with those
anonymous people online?

01:21:19.900 --> 01:21:21.760
FINLAY WILSON: Yeah, totally--

01:21:21.760 --> 01:21:25.000
I remember sharing,
I think it was

01:21:25.000 --> 01:21:27.910
when I shared about Scotland
getting same-sex marriage.

01:21:27.910 --> 01:21:28.570
I shared that.

01:21:28.570 --> 01:21:31.270
And one of our friends were
like, this is a travesty.

01:21:31.270 --> 01:21:32.590
And I wrote a letter to them.

01:21:32.590 --> 01:21:35.600
And I said, look, I
need you to acknowledge

01:21:35.600 --> 01:21:39.509
that by saying this, you are
invalidating me as a person.

01:21:39.509 --> 01:21:42.050
You're saying I don't deserve
to have the same rights as you.

01:21:42.050 --> 01:21:44.450
But you still think
that we can be friends.

01:21:44.450 --> 01:21:48.050
I cannot be friends with you if
this is how you're going to be.

01:21:48.050 --> 01:21:49.100
I cannot.

01:21:49.100 --> 01:21:52.220
I'm not going to whore
myself out so that you

01:21:52.220 --> 01:21:53.436
feel more comfortable.

01:21:53.436 --> 01:21:56.820
I'm not going to downplay
myself so that you feel better

01:21:56.820 --> 01:21:57.480
about yourself.

01:21:57.480 --> 01:21:59.940
I'm not doing it, no way.

01:21:59.940 --> 01:22:01.669
So get back on there.

01:22:01.669 --> 01:22:02.460
AOIFE MARTIN: Yeah.

01:22:02.460 --> 01:22:04.918
I mean, that's something I'm
struggling with at the moment.

01:22:04.918 --> 01:22:06.540
And I have family
members who don't

01:22:06.540 --> 01:22:09.390
accept who I am and expect--

01:22:09.390 --> 01:22:11.700
they still call me
by my birth name

01:22:11.700 --> 01:22:17.510
and won't meet me unless
I'm my former self.

01:22:17.510 --> 01:22:19.190
And I've just said, no.

01:22:19.190 --> 01:22:20.000
I'm not doing that.

01:22:20.000 --> 01:22:21.189
This is who I am.

01:22:21.189 --> 01:22:22.730
I've struggled with
this for so long.

01:22:22.730 --> 01:22:23.690
And I've come out.

01:22:23.690 --> 01:22:25.530
And I'm not going to
go back into that role.

01:22:25.530 --> 01:22:28.940
And if you can't
accept that, then we'll

01:22:28.940 --> 01:22:30.720
just have to not see each other.

01:22:30.720 --> 01:22:32.684
And it's hurtful.

01:22:32.684 --> 01:22:34.850
FINLAY WILSON: I would for
you to be part of my life

01:22:34.850 --> 01:22:36.420
and accept me for who I am.

01:22:36.420 --> 01:22:39.110
And if you cannot do that, then
I'm not going to change for you

01:22:39.110 --> 01:22:41.190
to be in part of my life.

01:22:41.190 --> 01:22:42.549
It's legit.

01:22:42.549 --> 01:22:44.090
I mean, I had some
family members not

01:22:44.090 --> 01:22:45.006
show up to my wedding.

01:22:45.006 --> 01:22:46.599
And it was like, I hear you.

01:22:46.599 --> 01:22:47.390
AOIFE MARTIN: Yeah.

01:22:47.390 --> 01:22:48.098
This is who I am.

01:22:48.098 --> 01:22:48.740
And that's it.

01:22:48.740 --> 01:22:50.315
I can't change it.

01:22:50.315 --> 01:22:51.320
Or sorry, I can.

01:22:51.320 --> 01:22:52.220
But I'm not going to.

01:22:55.496 --> 01:22:56.870
FINLAY WILSON:
You are being you.

01:22:56.870 --> 01:22:58.610
They are the ones
exerting the choice

01:22:58.610 --> 01:23:01.480
to be the bigoted asshole.

01:23:01.480 --> 01:23:03.910
JULIEN FINLAY: They
identify as assholes.

01:23:03.910 --> 01:23:05.156
That's [INAUDIBLE].

01:23:05.156 --> 01:23:06.280
You had a question as well?

01:23:10.300 --> 01:23:11.230
Raising hands?

01:23:11.230 --> 01:23:12.010
Nodding heads?

01:23:15.269 --> 01:23:17.310
AUDIENCE: I, too, love
the sound of my own voice.

01:23:17.310 --> 01:23:21.540
No, really quickly, it's
mostly to do with the amount

01:23:21.540 --> 01:23:23.370
of attention we give hate.

01:23:23.370 --> 01:23:25.200
So I know that
we've spoken a lot,

01:23:25.200 --> 01:23:28.170
and the panel has said a
lot, about the comments

01:23:28.170 --> 01:23:30.480
they remember, these
hateful, spiteful comments.

01:23:30.480 --> 01:23:33.030
But we haven't once
mentioned those good comments

01:23:33.030 --> 01:23:35.070
that we do get on those posts.

01:23:35.070 --> 01:23:37.987
And is it that really-- and this
is directed to both of you--

01:23:37.987 --> 01:23:39.570
that we are giving
too much attention?

01:23:39.570 --> 01:23:40.861
We are remembering these posts.

01:23:40.861 --> 01:23:42.720
And therefore, we're
glorifying them.

01:23:42.720 --> 01:23:45.780
I mean, even with the media,
we have celebrities reading out

01:23:45.780 --> 01:23:46.590
mean tweets.

01:23:46.590 --> 01:23:48.840
They don't read out the ones
that are nice about them.

01:23:48.840 --> 01:23:51.209
So is it that we are
creating this cycle?

01:23:51.209 --> 01:23:53.250
Because we are giving too
much attention to those

01:23:53.250 --> 01:23:53.850
hateful posts.

01:23:53.850 --> 01:23:57.450
And therefore, we're just
encouraging that kind

01:23:57.450 --> 01:23:59.010
of negative attention.

01:23:59.010 --> 01:24:00.930
FINLAY WILSON: I feel
like the positive--

01:24:00.930 --> 01:24:03.090
I aim to acknowledge
the positive as much

01:24:03.090 --> 01:24:05.400
as the negative when it
comes in as comments.

01:24:05.400 --> 01:24:08.340
Obviously, I will respond to
the positive with a lot more

01:24:08.340 --> 01:24:11.050
empathy and kindness.

01:24:11.050 --> 01:24:14.020
But the negative, it's that what
we were speaking about earlier.

01:24:14.020 --> 01:24:17.060
If we don't address the fact
that the negative is happening,

01:24:17.060 --> 01:24:19.600
it's not going to
make it go away.

01:24:19.600 --> 01:24:21.730
And if we pretend that
it isn't happening,

01:24:21.730 --> 01:24:23.690
then we are complicit.

01:24:23.690 --> 01:24:26.650
And I think that's the danger.

01:24:26.650 --> 01:24:30.270
Certainly, when people
message me and I ask,

01:24:30.270 --> 01:24:33.322
can I share your comment
because it was really lovely,

01:24:33.322 --> 01:24:34.780
some [INAUDIBLE]
the right to say--

01:24:34.780 --> 01:24:35.720
some say no.

01:24:35.720 --> 01:24:38.040
And so I don't get to
share some of that stuff.

01:24:38.040 --> 01:24:40.330
So I can't share or
repost a lot of stuff.

01:24:40.330 --> 01:24:42.670
But when I can, I do.

01:24:42.670 --> 01:24:45.440
But it is that thing of like,
if the negative comes in

01:24:45.440 --> 01:24:49.580
and we don't actually address
it, then it does start--

01:24:49.580 --> 01:24:51.800
it normalizes that.

01:24:51.800 --> 01:24:55.670
And that's, I think, both
of us standing up and being

01:24:55.670 --> 01:24:58.150
these voices that
speak out like that.

01:24:58.150 --> 01:25:00.170
I want the young kids
that I would teach

01:25:00.170 --> 01:25:01.730
to know that that's not OK.

01:25:01.730 --> 01:25:03.313
If somebody says
that to them, they're

01:25:03.313 --> 01:25:06.140
just going to quietly put it
to bed and then just go home.

01:25:06.140 --> 01:25:12.410
It might raise in them
that same fire to resist.

01:25:12.410 --> 01:25:13.729
Does that make sense?

01:25:13.729 --> 01:25:14.520
AOIFE MARTIN: Yeah.

01:25:14.520 --> 01:25:18.310
I think just being nice is
sort of the default position.

01:25:18.310 --> 01:25:19.890
I mean, it shouldn't be.

01:25:19.890 --> 01:25:22.680
It's not a hard line
to achieve, I think.

01:25:22.680 --> 01:25:26.670
And 90% of the
stuff I get online

01:25:26.670 --> 01:25:28.630
is positive and is
very, very kind.

01:25:28.630 --> 01:25:30.240
And people are very,
very supportive.

01:25:30.240 --> 01:25:36.150
It's that 10% of negativity,
where you want to address that.

01:25:36.150 --> 01:25:39.100
And you want to say,
look, this is out there.

01:25:39.100 --> 01:25:42.210
And if we don't talk about
it or if we don't address it,

01:25:42.210 --> 01:25:43.950
it's just going to spread.

01:25:43.950 --> 01:25:48.270
And there is the thing
about, again, not

01:25:48.270 --> 01:25:52.290
conforming people, not
conforming Nazis and giving

01:25:52.290 --> 01:25:54.870
them voices on the
media, and not performing

01:25:54.870 --> 01:25:57.810
certain viewpoints is,
I think there is a lot

01:25:57.810 --> 01:26:00.940
to be said for that as well,
in that certain things aren't

01:26:00.940 --> 01:26:01.440
a debate.

01:26:01.440 --> 01:26:02.640
My life is not a debate.

01:26:02.640 --> 01:26:07.230
But I think this week on
one of the BBC channels,

01:26:07.230 --> 01:26:12.560
there was a guy on who said he
identified as 20 years younger.

01:26:12.560 --> 01:26:14.820
And so they had a trans
woman on, debating with him.

01:26:14.820 --> 01:26:16.330
I'm going, why are
you doing this?

01:26:16.330 --> 01:26:18.480
Why are you equating
this with somebody

01:26:18.480 --> 01:26:19.830
who has gender dysphoria?

01:26:19.830 --> 01:26:21.520
It's a completely
different issue.

01:26:21.520 --> 01:26:24.090
But in the minds of the popular,
they're going, oh, yeah.

01:26:24.090 --> 01:26:26.631
If that guy is silly, obviously,
trans people are silly, too.

01:26:26.631 --> 01:26:28.860
Because how can you identify
as something you're not?

01:26:28.860 --> 01:26:30.943
FINLAY WILSON: I mean, I
identify as a helicopter.

01:26:30.943 --> 01:26:34.774
And it's just like, this
is not what is being said,

01:26:34.774 --> 01:26:35.940
it's not what is being said.

01:26:36.187 --> 01:26:38.520
AOIFE MARTIN: There was an
article in the "Sunday Times"

01:26:38.520 --> 01:26:40.470
this week, where Rod
Liddle said, oh, I

01:26:40.470 --> 01:26:42.995
want to identify as a
black trans chihuahua.

01:26:42.995 --> 01:26:45.314
I was like, all
you're doing is just

01:26:45.314 --> 01:26:46.980
saying hurtful things
about trans people

01:26:46.980 --> 01:26:48.480
by putting that as an article.

01:26:48.480 --> 01:26:49.310
FINLAY WILSON: Acknowledging
that there is--

01:26:49.310 --> 01:26:50.925
AOIFE MARTIN: You're
negating our experience.

01:26:50.925 --> 01:26:52.549
FINLAY WILSON: --but
also acknowledging

01:26:52.549 --> 01:26:54.480
marginalized hurt and
then making fun of it.

01:26:54.480 --> 01:26:55.750
AOIFE MARTIN: Yeah.

01:26:55.750 --> 01:26:58.920
FINLAY WILSON:
That's really not OK.

01:26:58.920 --> 01:27:02.490
So almost thinking about
the negativity, what

01:27:02.490 --> 01:27:04.740
was happening in the airport
first thing this morning,

01:27:04.740 --> 01:27:07.239
admittedly, it was an ungodly
hour that I was in the airport

01:27:07.239 --> 01:27:08.010
this morning.

01:27:08.010 --> 01:27:14.070
But a simple act of
speaking out can do wonders.

01:27:14.070 --> 01:27:17.970
The simple act of picking
up the trays at security

01:27:17.970 --> 01:27:20.130
and putting them back,
because it was backing up

01:27:20.130 --> 01:27:22.410
because nobody had
the basic courtesy

01:27:22.410 --> 01:27:23.737
to pick up their own damn tray.

01:27:23.737 --> 01:27:25.320
So I picked up five
and put them away.

01:27:25.320 --> 01:27:27.000
And suddenly, everything
was easy again.

01:27:27.000 --> 01:27:30.240
So in the face of an
onslaught of negativity,

01:27:30.240 --> 01:27:33.690
if we don't speak out
about it, it mounts up.

01:27:33.690 --> 01:27:37.800
And without sounding
militant, they

01:27:37.800 --> 01:27:42.100
begin to win because they
don't meet any resistance.

01:27:42.100 --> 01:27:45.190
And they expect us to
just quietly resist.

01:27:45.190 --> 01:27:47.287
And it's not the time for that.

01:27:47.287 --> 01:27:49.370
I mean, rights have been
stripped away in America.

01:27:49.370 --> 01:27:52.720
Now if I go into a restaurant
in America with my partner,

01:27:52.720 --> 01:27:54.400
they can refuse
service on the basis

01:27:54.400 --> 01:27:57.290
that we are a same-sex couple.

01:27:57.290 --> 01:27:59.780
That's disgusting.

01:27:59.780 --> 01:28:03.980
And what happens in the
States could happen in the UK

01:28:03.980 --> 01:28:06.770
just as easily.

01:28:06.770 --> 01:28:09.200
These opinions aren't small.

01:28:09.200 --> 01:28:11.840
These aren't being said
by insignificant people.

01:28:11.840 --> 01:28:15.850
Some of the trolls run
countries, you know?

01:28:15.850 --> 01:28:17.269
That's frightening.

01:28:17.269 --> 01:28:18.060
That's frightening.

01:28:18.060 --> 01:28:19.397
And trans rights as well--

01:28:19.397 --> 01:28:21.230
there was something
that went out just about

01:28:21.230 --> 01:28:23.480
two weeks ago in the States,
where they're saying, actually,

01:28:23.480 --> 01:28:25.550
trans people now need
to have a genetic test

01:28:25.550 --> 01:28:29.850
to say what their
actual birth gender is

01:28:29.850 --> 01:28:31.314
through genetic testing.

01:28:31.314 --> 01:28:33.730
JULIEN FINLAY: Focusing on the
right and the good comments

01:28:33.730 --> 01:28:34.870
instead of the wrong.

01:28:34.870 --> 01:28:36.040
All right.

01:28:36.040 --> 01:28:39.220
On this note, so
we come to the end.

01:28:39.220 --> 01:28:42.100
We have some bubbles
and non-bubbles

01:28:42.100 --> 01:28:43.334
and biscuits and whatever.

01:28:43.334 --> 01:28:44.500
They're just waiting for us.

01:28:44.500 --> 01:28:47.260
They made a big bang
when I started talking.

01:28:47.260 --> 01:28:51.710
Do you have any other questions,
or shall I close this?

01:28:51.710 --> 01:28:52.530
Good.

01:28:52.530 --> 01:28:56.070
So I'll leave the floor to you
to just give your final words.

01:28:56.070 --> 01:28:58.200
You're not going to die
again in shamanic way,

01:28:58.200 --> 01:29:00.136
but just to say goodbye.

01:29:00.136 --> 01:29:02.260
FINLAY WILSON: You've all
gone through it together.

01:29:02.260 --> 01:29:03.650
JULIEN FINLAY: Let's do it.

01:29:03.650 --> 01:29:05.608
But anyway, it was a real
pleasure hosting you,

01:29:05.608 --> 01:29:06.900
a real pleasure having you.

01:29:06.900 --> 01:29:10.200
We discussed education and
how can somehow we prevent

01:29:10.200 --> 01:29:12.930
hate before it's already there?

01:29:12.930 --> 01:29:16.380
And once it's there, how can
we cope by resisting it and not

01:29:16.380 --> 01:29:20.490
just focusing on itself,
not giving it a platform,

01:29:20.490 --> 01:29:23.430
but really seeing the other
alternative, like other apps,

01:29:23.430 --> 01:29:25.530
or thinking how we
actually all play a role,

01:29:25.530 --> 01:29:28.680
like in the airports, lifting
and helping other people?

01:29:28.680 --> 01:29:30.090
So thank you again.

01:29:30.090 --> 01:29:31.380
We're going to clap once.

01:29:31.380 --> 01:29:33.770
We're going to talk and hear
you say your last words.

01:29:33.770 --> 01:29:34.620
And we clap again.

01:29:34.620 --> 01:29:39.090
[APPLAUSE]

01:29:39.090 --> 01:29:40.520
Final words, Aoife?

01:29:40.520 --> 01:29:42.410
AOIFE MARTIN: Final
words words of wisdom--

01:29:42.410 --> 01:29:44.050
just first of all,
thank you very much.

01:29:44.050 --> 01:29:47.350
It's been an absolute privilege
and an honor to be here.

01:29:47.350 --> 01:29:51.930
And it's just about
getting voices out there.

01:29:51.930 --> 01:29:55.770
And I think I do what
I do because I grew up

01:29:55.770 --> 01:29:57.460
with no representation.

01:29:57.460 --> 01:30:00.720
And if by what I say
and by what I do,

01:30:00.720 --> 01:30:02.490
I can help one young
trans person out

01:30:02.490 --> 01:30:03.660
there feel better
about themselves

01:30:03.660 --> 01:30:05.326
or feel more accepting
about themselves,

01:30:05.326 --> 01:30:06.490
then it's worthwhile.

01:30:06.490 --> 01:30:07.800
And that's the only
reason I do what I do.

01:30:07.800 --> 01:30:09.008
It's the only reason I speak.

01:30:09.008 --> 01:30:10.710
And it's the only reason I talk.

01:30:10.710 --> 01:30:11.665
Thank you very much.

01:30:11.665 --> 01:30:14.040
FINLAY WILSON: So one of the
motivators behind my actions

01:30:14.040 --> 01:30:15.360
on a daily basis,
one of the things

01:30:15.360 --> 01:30:17.040
that we instill in the
kids that we teach,

01:30:17.040 --> 01:30:19.415
one of the things we instill
in the adults that we teach,

01:30:19.415 --> 01:30:22.020
and especially in how they act
when they leave the yoga room,

01:30:22.020 --> 01:30:23.820
is to ask the
question, does what

01:30:23.820 --> 01:30:29.170
I'm about to do, say, write,
brighten or dim my spirit?

01:30:29.170 --> 01:30:30.960
And if you can answer
it, saying that it

01:30:30.960 --> 01:30:34.410
is going to bolster you, do it.

01:30:34.410 --> 01:30:36.570
If you are swearing
that you're going

01:30:36.570 --> 01:30:40.822
to end up like a toxic slime
ball, why are you doing that?

01:30:40.822 --> 01:30:42.280
So if you can be
comfortable enough

01:30:42.280 --> 01:30:44.196
with yourself to know
that what you are doing,

01:30:44.196 --> 01:30:46.660
what your actions are,
are building your energy,

01:30:46.660 --> 01:30:50.230
building your life force,
do that thing, creativity,

01:30:50.230 --> 01:30:52.990
make things, help people.

01:30:52.990 --> 01:30:56.440
But if you start doing something
else, you are damaging.

01:30:56.440 --> 01:30:59.185
And be aware of it, because
we're going to get you.

01:30:59.185 --> 01:30:59.872
[LAUGHTER]

01:30:59.872 --> 01:31:02.330
JULIEN FINLAY: Well, I'm sure
you both brighten up our day.

01:31:02.330 --> 01:31:06.070
So thank you and goodbye.

01:31:06.070 --> 01:31:08.820
[APPLAUSE]

